    "body": "## Purpose\r\n\r\nFix FlashInfer attention crashing when `kv_cache_dtype_skip_layers` is used (introduced in #33695).\r\n\r\nThe metadata builder read the global `cache_config.cache_dtype` (e.g., `\"fp8\"`) instead of the per-group `kv_cache_spec.kv_quant_mode`, so skipped layers were still treated as fp8. \r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\nOn B200s (where FlashInfer attention is default) \r\n```bash\r\n.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/quantization/test_fp8.py::test_kv_cache_dtype_skip_layers -v\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Test Result\r\n\r\nBefore:\r\n\r\n```\r\n(EngineCore pid=3740593)   File \"/home/yzong-rh/vllm/vllm/v1/attention/backends/flashinfer.py\", line 1313, in forward\r\n(EngineCore pid=3740593)     assert attn_metadata.q_data_type == query.dtype, (\r\n(EngineCore pid=3740593)            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n(EngineCore pid=3740593) AssertionError: Query dtype mismatch: expected torch.float8_e4m3fn, got torch.float16\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter the fix, the test passes.\r\n\r\n---\r\n<details>\r\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\r\n\r\n- [x] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\r\n- [x] The test plan, such as providing test command.\r\n- [x] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\r\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\r\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\r\n</details>",
